reviews.review_text:
One more set! This is the source I had  for year back in the 1980's, and it is very nice to see it was drawn from a PCM source. It is an exceptional powerhouse performance. Jerry is more reserved and sweet,hence Ship of Fools  followed by the  bust out of Crazy Finger, but  turns up the heat continually with plenty or raging runs, while Bobby is  the complete rock star on this night. 

A " standard" looking 1st set on paper is hardly the case.. as it resembles a set from 1977, and is played with bravado!
Set II is a  wonderful and joyous experience from beginning to end. In the early 1980's Franklin's Tower could turn up anywhere and this  version is rollicking.

The only " new" tune this show is Women is Smarter and Jerry is just dancing on water for this one. Bobby is a  hoot and doesn't want it to end either.

Phil is dropping  bombs the entire  night, and he does  saturate this source very often but I do prefer this version compared to the other sources. Jerry and the drums sounds quite  good as does Brent.

This was really the fuse that lite the fire of this amazing mid summer tour that would wander through the inter mountain and  Midwest ending in Iowa City. This tour is one of my favorite and every night has something quite special and the ensemble playing by all is top notch.

Plus it  was Phil's second to last tour with his  four string and he is all over it...big time!

Happy trails.
